# Adaptive RAG Research Project — Step-by-Step

**Thesis**: "Similarity score distributions are structured, query-dependent signals. We characterize their shape taxonomy, use them for adaptive retrieval, and show confidence scores predict answer quality without ground truth."

---

## Phase 0 — Foundation Stabilization (Week 1–2)

### Week 1: Clean Baseline + Score Collection
- [ ] Clean up RAG code into reproducible single pipeline
- [ ] Fix BGE prefix consistently (query + ingestion)
- [ ] Set chunk_size=512, overlap=100, sentence-aware splitting
- [ ] Store similarity scores for every retrieval to CSV
- [ ] Add centralized config (`config.py`)
- [ ] Run on 100 queries, save full similarity score vectors

### Week 2: Evaluation Dataset + Baseline Metrics
- [ ] Auto-generate 200 Q&A pairs from Yelp docs using Mistral 7B
- [ ] Hand-curate 50 high-quality ground truth pairs
- [ ] Run baseline system on all 200, record P@K, R@K, similarity vectors
- [ ] Save all curves to disk → raw research data
- [ ] Produce deliverable CSV: `query_id, query_text, type_label, similarity_scores, P@5, R@5, faithfulness`

---

## Phase 1 — Core Scientific Finding (Week 3–5)
- [ ] Compute per-curve features: kurtosis, slope, bimodality, entropy
- [ ] K-means clustering (k=3-4) on shape features
- [ ] Plot cluster centroids → discover shape taxonomy
- [ ] Logistic regression: shape features → answer correctness (AUC)
- [ ] Cross-domain validation on CUAD dataset

## Phase 2 — Build Adaptive System (Week 6–9)
- [ ] Embedding-based intent classifier with prototypes
- [ ] Adaptive retriever with shape-aware trimming strategies
- [ ] Confidence score: mean(selected_sims) / max(sim)
- [ ] Prompt template selection by query complexity

## Phase 3 — Comprehensive Evaluation (Week 10–12)
- [ ] 5-system baseline comparison (Static-K3/K5, Intent-K, QA-RAG, Oracle-K)
- [ ] Calibration experiment (confidence vs faithfulness)
- [ ] Ablation study

## Phase 4 — Paper Writing (Week 13–16)
- [ ] Sections 3→4→5→2→1→Abstract
